I created a Page (named overview) and three childpages. On every child page there is an excerpt macro with an attachment macro inside.

On the overview page, I included all three excerpts from the childpages, so I get 3 attachment areas on one page.

If I click on the upload function in one of these macros the file will be uploaded to the childpage. That's what I want. But if I drag & drop a file into one of the three attachment areas, the file will be uploaded to the overview page instead.

Steps to reproduce:

* Create a space
* Go to *Space tools* > *Look and Feel*
* Choose *Documentation theme*
* Click on *Configure theme*
* In *Messages*, add the following to Header (or Footer):
{code}
{section}
{column:width=23%}
{panel:title=Table of Contents|borderColor=#999999|borderStyle=solid|titleColor=#999999|bgColor=#FFFFFF|titleBGColor=#FFFFFF}
{toc:style=disc}
{panel}
{column}
{column:width=23%}
{panel:title=Releases|borderColor=#999999|borderStyle=solid|titleColor=#999999|bgColor=#FFFFFF|titleBGColor=#FFFFFF}
{subspaces:style=plain|key=TS|maxDepth=0|sort=title}
{panel}
{column}
{column:width=23%}
{panel:title=Quick Links|borderColor=#999999|borderStyle=solid|titleColor=#999999|bgColor=#FFFFFF|titleBGColor=#FFFFFF}
[Atlassian|http://www.atlassian.com/]
{link-to:add comment|linkText=Add page Comment}
{link-to:page comments|linkText=View page Comments}
{link-to:page attachments|linkText=Add Attachment}
{link-to:pdf export|linkText=Export page to PDF}
{link-to:word export|linkText=Export page to Word}
{panel}
{column}
{section}
{code}
* Save the changes and access the space Home Page

In version 4.3.7 you will see the text is aligned to the left:

 !Screen Shot 2016-06-02 at 15.23.13.png|thumbnail! 

In version 5.8.18 (or any version 5.x, tested in Confluence 5.0, 5.3, 5.7 and 5.8.18) you will see the text is centralized:
 
 !Screen Shot 2016-06-02 at 15.29.30.png|thumbnail!

