On our confluence wiki page at Apache we have been adding tutorials and workflows. In the past not many developers used Twitter / social networks as they do today. Now, Twitter, G+ and other networks are part of developers lives to share news and updates on their projects. Wiki pages would benefit from social sharing features like Twitter, Google +1, and 'Share' (with an email address). Followers on Twitter would benefit from us sharing updates and news. 

Related wiki [https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=63406558].
Note: There is a share button at the top of a wiki page but it requires you to login and does not include social networks.

